# Test-Driven Development Rules

See [docs/testing.md](../../docs/testing.md) for comprehensive testing guidelines, examples, and best practices.

## TDD Workflow

When writing or modifying code:

1. Write/update a failing test first
2. Implement minimal code to pass
3. Refactor while green
4. Repeat

When fixing bugs: update existing test to fail, then fix.

## Test Generation Checklist

When generating tests, ensure:

- [ ] Outer `describe` names the component/function/feature
- [ ] Nested `describe` blocks define contexts: `when <condition>`
- [ ] `it` blocks use behavior names: `should <behavior>`
- [ ] Test body has Given/When/Then comments
- [ ] Only observable behavior is asserted (not internals)
- [ ] External dependencies are mocked
- [ ] Mocks reset in `beforeEach`

## Coverage Enforcement

- Unit tests: 100% required
- E2E tests: validation only, no coverage
- Exceptions: `/* v8 ignore next */` with justification

## Anti-Patterns

Reject tests that:

- Test private methods or implementation details
- Have multiple actions (multiple "When" steps)
- Assert exact error message strings
- Use large object snapshots
- Assert ordering unless contractually required
- Duplicate existing test coverage
